-- England Loses 22-17 in Opening Game of South Africa Rugby Tour
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-06-09T17:19:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-09/england-loses-22-17-in-opening-game-of-south-africa-rugby-tour.html
Morne Steyn and Jean de Villiers
scored second-half tries as South Africa beat England 22-17 in
their opening rugby Test in Durban.  Steyne also kicked four penalties for the Springboks, who
outscored England 16-11 in the second half. South Africa has won
eight straight games against England, the longest run by either
team in 33 Test matches between them.  Ben Foden  scored a try in the final seconds for England and
Owen Farrell booted four penalties.  The three-Test series continues in Johannesburg on June 16
and  Port Elizabeth  on June 23.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  